00:00.000 --> 00:08.200
In 1987, the International Space University was founded to develop and implement international

00:08.200 --> 00:10.720
space-related curriculum.

00:10.720 --> 00:15.360
This university would identify, assemble, and educate a new generation of young leaders

00:15.360 --> 00:17.000
from around the world.

00:17.000 --> 00:22.360
By uniting these students in an intensive program of study and research, ISU would foster

00:22.360 --> 00:27.840
long-lasting ties between these future heads of industry, government, and academia, creating

00:27.840 --> 00:33.680
an international network, which would help assure cooperation in the opening of space.

00:33.680 --> 00:39.960
In the summer of 1988, that mission was accomplished, and the International Space University

00:39.960 --> 00:42.200
was born.

00:42.200 --> 00:48.360
For the first summer session of the International Space University, 104 of the world's top graduate

00:48.360 --> 00:53.400
level students from 21 nations came together on the campus of the Massachusetts Institute

00:53.400 --> 00:55.680
of Technology.

00:55.680 --> 01:00.720
Having undergone a rigorous selection program, these students participated in an experience

01:00.720 --> 01:05.720
